        "timestamp": "2021-02-08 06:43:24.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 3:\n\nyou applied this patch to guilin branch\nin Guilin we fixed the version of the lib to 7.3.0 so it is working fine...\nhttps://logs.onap.org/onap-integration/daily/onap_daily_pod4_guilin/02-08-2021_03-02/\n\nthe issue is now on the master branch (which is used for master weely/daily and gating CI/CD chains), which used to consume the latest version of python-onapsdk\n\nSo I would apply this patch only on master first\nand if OK cherry-pick to guilin to backport the change and use the 7.4.0\n\nRegarding the remark from Sylvain, as the pythonsdk-tests are used on master and gating, we need to find a procedure to be more careful on sdk update... We could use the develop branch of pythonsdk-tests to give a try on the openlab, then when it is validated we merge it to master. I need to formalize something here, I will share by mail.\n\notherwise for the gating, another option would be to use the latest stable (guilin here)?\nbut if we add a verification through the develop versions of the docker, it shall be safe enough for the chains.",
